2) cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of neural architectures for parsing and explores the effectiveness of typological information in such models. 
3) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques for natural language processing. 
4) cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a relevant category as the paper focuses on neural architectures for parsing. 
5) cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss distributed training of neural models for parsing.
